    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-01-23T00:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-01-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="61"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d61">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/3613: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China (<persName corresp="#p_JNT1" type="from"
                            >Johnson</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-01-23T13:00:00+08:00"
                            >January 23, 1932—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received January 23—2:40 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>113. Following from American Consul General at Harbin: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“January 21, 5 p.m. Commissioner of Foreign Affairs informed <persName
                                corresp="#p_CSA1">Chamberlain</persName> today that
                                <persName>Pinhsien</persName> last bombed on 16th and Yuanshu,
                            Wuchang and neighboring places last few days, Japanese aeroplane flew
                            over Harbin yesterday, that <persName corresp="#p_CJ1">Cheng
                                Jun</persName>, head of the <persName>Pinhsien</persName>
                            Government, is determined to hold out against the new regime until the
                            receipt of orders from Nanking and mat local newspapers are so fearful
                            of Japanese influence that they dare not publish reports of bombing.</p>
                        <list>
                            <label>2.</label>
                            <item>I have no confirmation of reports of bombing. Japanese have
                                informed me that it is sure that agreement has been reached whereby
                                    <persName>Pinhsien</persName> Government will be dissolved. I
                                believe that it cannot maintain itself.</item>
                            <label>3.</label>
                            <item>
                                <persName corresp="#p_OC1">Ohashi</persName> left Harbin by airplane
                                for Mukden yesterday evidently to consult with the Japanese there
                                and later at Kirin.</item>
                            <label>4.</label>
                            <item>It is reported that <persName corresp="#p_DCK1">Doihara</persName>
                                left Tokyo for Harbin yesterday. His expected arrival here is looked
                                upon with apprehension by the Chinese authorities.”</item>
                        </list>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_JNT1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
